comment: There's two bathroom stalls one is "ladies" and the other just says "anybodies". Most Irish people wouldn't say anything if you went into either male or female labelled bathroom stalls in any facility but just to be safe or if it makes you anxious, anybodies in the roadhouse is a safe bet x (also pretty great if you're gender fluid because anybodies is pretty general)

name: Shell On Tecumseh-Clinton Rd
directions: Back right corner of the store. Two gendered locking single stall restrooms. Hours are 24/7, you have to be buzzed through the front door at certain times of the night.
comment: Open 24 Hours. Some employees, especially daytime cashiers (two younger women, if it's the tattooed guy or the older lady you're fine), are openly transphobic - don't make eye contact with them and don't buy anything if you don't want to be bothered. They won't stop you from using the bathroom, but they will very pointedly misgender you if you speak with them. Especially if you're a trans woman/transfeminine. Welcome to Clinton :/
